{"id":14881789,"mediaExerciseId":"9006616d-e679-4439-ab36-ad929188cc2d","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612473,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":739,"solutions":[{"id":5996286,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked if what will happen to the company's profit if the dollar strengthens or weakens.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/c490821fcb52efd1b1875dd0e3d5feb7/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/c490821fcb52efd1b1875dd0e3d5feb7/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In the minicase, S&S wanted to sell their planes in Europe.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"When the dollar **strengthens**, its value will increased. Hence, more euros is required to exchange into dollars. If they will convert their sales in euros to dollars, fewer dollars will be obtained. As a result, the company will incur a **loss** on the foreign exchange rate. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/7feb770828aa13fc07b1151a09b9bc85/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/7feb770828aa13fc07b1151a09b9bc85/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, when the dollar **weakens**, its value will decreased. Hence, lesser euros is required to exchange into dollars. If they will convert their sales in Euros to dollars, more dollars will be obtained. As a result, the company will incur a **gain** on the foreign exchange rate. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/908142ffc6c5e4b3829b33bb9b2c034c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/908142ffc6c5e4b3829b33bb9b2c034c/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, if the dollar **strengthens**, the company will incur a **loss**. On the other hand, if the dollar **weakens**, the company will incur a **gain**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/179b902c2cc462a6d0fbcb3f78460549/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/b870f1508c560b1dc137cf640277afda/179b902c2cc462a6d0fbcb3f78460549/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"15ce63d3-c33d-41eb-b32d-2eba96a97ed4","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":16654